00:37:38,360 --> 00:37:40,202
Oh dear, what have I done here?

369
00:37:42,284 --> 00:37:45,608
Oh dear, dear, dear.

370
00:37:45,628 --> 00:37:46,228
Oh dear.

371
00:37:46,730 --> 00:37:48,050
I've messed up this particular.

372
00:37:48,672 --> 00:37:52,115
I wanted to read out this.

373
00:37:56,541 --> 00:37:56,701
Oh dear.

374
00:37:56,721 --> 00:37:57,422
Oh, wait a minute.

375
00:37:57,442 --> 00:37:58,242
Let's see if I can...

376
00:38:03,251 --> 00:38:08,257
I enlarged something that was a photograph and it's not, half of it's hidden.

377
00:38:08,777 --> 00:38:11,481
So I'm gonna see if I can just draw it down a bit.

378
00:38:13,143 --> 00:38:14,463
It's working on it, here we go.

379
00:38:17,027 --> 00:38:22,833
This is the bit to do with karma when I get to it.

380
00:38:27,978 --> 00:38:31,282
Right, here we are.

381
00:38:31,302 --> 00:38:32,262
Here we are.

382
00:38:39,769 --> 00:38:45,639
Okay.

383
00:38:45,659 --> 00:38:45,920
Yes.

384
00:38:45,940 --> 00:38:46,039
Okay.

385
00:38:46,561 --> 00:38:54,753
So one of the misunderstandings of karma is of course that everything that happens to us is karma.

386
00:38:55,876 --> 00:39:06,773
Any bad feelings we have, et cetera, physical anyway, is because in the past life we did something terrible, or even in this life we did something terrible.

387
00:39:07,293 --> 00:39:09,836
And the Buddha is quite clear about that.

388
00:39:10,018 --> 00:39:11,579
That doesn't hold.

389
00:39:11,679 --> 00:39:14,003
So Sivaka, the song to purse called Sivaka.

390
00:39:14,605 --> 00:39:18,090
Some feelings arise on account of irregularities in the bile.

391
00:39:19,092 --> 00:39:21,436
Some on account of irregularities in the phlegm.

392
00:39:21,757 --> 00:39:23,559
Some in account of wind.

393
00:39:23,960 --> 00:39:26,545
Some on account of the confluence of numerous factors.

394
00:39:26,644 --> 00:39:28,547
Some on account of changes in the weather.

395
00:39:29,369 --> 00:39:31,393
Some account of irregular exercise.

396
00:39:31,626 --> 00:39:36,452
some on account of external dangers, some on the account of karma results.

397
00:39:36,974 --> 00:39:39,016
So after all these, there are results from karma.

398
00:39:40,277 --> 00:39:46,766
That feelings arise dependent on these different causes is something you can see for yourself and that people everywhere acknowledge.

399
00:39:47,206 --> 00:39:53,094
On this account, any recluse or holy man who claims all feelings that arise, be they pleasant or unpleasant,

400
00:39:53,581 --> 00:40:01,152
are entirely the result of previous karma, can be rightly said to have spoken in excess of what is obvious to people everywhere.

401
00:40:01,532 --> 00:40:03,476
And I say that such views are wrong.

402
00:40:06,260 --> 00:40:17,858
So that confusion is not just in present day Buddhists, but also in that time where everything was seen as fate.

403
00:40:17,878 --> 00:40:22,525
There were teachers who taught that everything that happened to you is caused because of past karma.

404
00:40:23,146 --> 00:40:26,128
And his argument would be, what about what you do now?

405
00:40:26,550 --> 00:40:27,289
What is the effect?

406
00:40:27,751 --> 00:40:29,873
If you do something now, it has an effect on you.

407
00:40:30,434 --> 00:40:35,199
So it's not just the past coming at you, it's your decisions that you make now which have effect.

408
00:40:37,041 --> 00:40:46,210
Monks, when there is an intentional, fixed and steady deliberation on any theme, that theme becomes an object for sustained consciousness.

409
00:40:47,050 --> 00:40:50,655
Where there is an object, consciousness has an abiding object.

410
00:40:51,309 --> 00:40:57,416
When consciousness is so firmly established and developed, birth in the new sphere ensues.

411
00:40:57,456 --> 00:40:58,137
That's the becoming.

412
00:40:58,777 --> 00:41:05,143
And when there arises into a new sphere of existence, birth, old age, death, sorrow, lamentation and pain.

413
00:41:05,164 --> 00:41:10,989
This is where the arising of this whole mass of suffering arises.

414
00:41:11,391 --> 00:41:13,552
This is where all that suffering arises.

415
00:41:14,474 --> 00:41:15,135
Oh, now you see.

416
00:41:17,858 --> 00:41:20,219
Once you're into correcting of

417
00:41:20,672 --> 00:41:35,295
So this is just something else that whatever happens to us now is not entirely dependent upon some past action.

418
00:41:35,315 --> 00:41:39,802
In fact, I would say a lot of things, most things aren't.

419
00:41:39,822 --> 00:41:47,472
It's just that to be able to distinguish why something has happened to us from some karmic act or from what's happening now

420
00:41:47,960 --> 00:41:51,025
The Buddha said, you know, try and work out your karma, drive you mad.

421
00:41:54,891 --> 00:42:08,536
But in terms of our inner life, you see, where there is an intentional fixed steady deliberation on a theme, where we're thinking about something, especially obsessively, that thing becomes the object of sustained consciousness.

422
00:42:08,635 --> 00:42:09,376
So it's not...

423
00:42:09,626 --> 00:42:13,474
And where there is an object, consciousness has an abiding, right?

424
00:42:13,554 --> 00:42:16,900
So the consciousness has an abiding in what you're actually thinking about.

425
00:42:17,521 --> 00:42:23,751
Now there is somewhere else where he actually says that the mind has its abiding in the body.

426
00:42:25,335 --> 00:42:33,289
If you remember on the earlier talk, we were wondering where was the sense base of the mind, right?

427
00:42:33,673 --> 00:42:37,097
So we know that with eyes, it's the retina and so on.

428
00:42:37,518 --> 00:42:39,380
So where's the mental sense base?

429
00:42:39,840 --> 00:42:43,204
So it becomes pretty clear that it's the whole body.

430
00:42:45,847 --> 00:42:51,655
So when consciousness is so firmly established and developed, then you get that rebirth, right?

431
00:42:51,735 --> 00:42:54,217
So that's your dependence origination, that's bhava.

432
00:42:54,958 --> 00:43:00,344
Now bhava here means not only intention, an empowered intention, right?

433
00:43:00,364 --> 00:43:01,385
An act of will, right?

434
00:43:01,771 --> 00:43:07,239
It is an action and the self recreates itself.

435
00:43:08,201 --> 00:43:13,349
So you're constantly recreating that sense of me through time.

436
00:43:13,409 --> 00:43:18,036
And it's because of this that all the rest of it happens.

437
00:43:18,516 --> 00:43:19,838
A new sphere of existence.

438
00:43:20,559 --> 00:43:24,887
Birth, old age, death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, grief and despair.

439
00:43:24,987 --> 00:43:25,568
That's quite a

440
00:43:26,003 --> 00:43:28,244
Quite a list, isn't it?

441
00:43:28,646 --> 00:43:31,288
This is the whole mass of suffering.

442
00:43:32,409 --> 00:43:42,619
So just to recap there, Vedana has its base in the initial contact.

443
00:43:43,699 --> 00:43:46,382
And then from then on, it's all mentation.

444
00:43:46,422 --> 00:43:49,105
It's all the mind working with feelings.

445
00:43:50,025 --> 00:43:54,070
And our lives are a jumble of these feelings.

446
00:43:54,909 --> 00:44:03,159
And the question is, what sort of mental state do I want to develop?

447
00:44:03,179 --> 00:44:06,302
What sort of mental state do I want to be in all the time?

448
00:44:07,043 --> 00:44:13,168
So if we look at the Buddha, we can presume that all that negativity had gone.

449
00:44:13,208 --> 00:44:22,639
So when he's in contact with somebody, the social virtues, love, compassion,

450
00:44:23,141 --> 00:44:28,231
joy, gratitude, they would all arise naturally as beautiful mental states.

451
00:44:28,992 --> 00:44:38,188
And when nobody's there, or when other people are there, but they're sitting quietly or whatever, the heart would just slowly come down to that equanimity.

452
00:44:38,728 --> 00:44:46,702
And that equanimity is the basis for all the other mental states, because it stops the other mental states falling into their

453
00:44:47,206 --> 00:44:51,032
Subtle enemies, near enemies sometimes, it's translated as so.

454
00:44:51,612 --> 00:44:57,161
Love towards affection, compassion towards grief and joy towards excitement.

455
00:44:57,882 --> 00:45:00,945
So that's where we want to get to, isn't it?

456
00:45:00,965 --> 00:45:09,619
We want to get to that underlying steady line of contentment, contentment and equanimity.

457
00:45:10,054 --> 00:45:13,159
And then you get these little pleasant blips that arrive.

458
00:45:13,358 --> 00:45:16,443
A bit of love, a bit of compassion, a bit of joy.

459
00:45:16,483 --> 00:45:21,429
And then just the silence of equanimity.

460
00:45:24,773 --> 00:45:30,920
So that's where we're heading over the next couple of days, of course.

461
00:45:33,405 --> 00:45:34,746
Or we can live in hope.

462
00:45:34,885 --> 00:45:35,387
Why not?

463
00:45:37,443 --> 00:45:42,990
So I can only hope my words have been of some assistance, that they have not caused even greater confusion.

464
00:45:43,532 --> 00:46:00,496
May you, by your constant effort to establish the right type of mental state, be fully liberated sooner rather than later.

